@NODE "Programm" "About the programm"
@prev "Vervielfältigung"
@next "AFDCopyright"
@{u}@{b}About the Program@{ub}@{uu}

Actual version: 37.54

This program is @{"MAILWARE" LINK "AFDCopyright" 76} (see @{"Distribution" LINK "Vervielfältigung"}).

@{b}WinCommodity@{ub} has prooven to be stable in everyday use
@{b}WinCommodity@{ub} was written in AmigaE and compiled using AmigaE v3.2e.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Funktionen" "The functions"

WinCommodity provides 7 functions this time:

 @{"CenterWins " LINK "CenterWins"} - centring the active Window
 @{"ParentWin  " LINK "ParentWin"} - move window below its previous one
 @{"ZipWin     " LINK "ZipWin"} - minimize/maximize the active window
 @{"CloseWin   " LINK "CloseWin"} - close the active window
 @{"CloseWBWins" LINK "CloseWBWins"} - close all workbenchwindows
 @{"ToggleWins " LINK "ToggleWins"} - activates the next window
 @{"TopLeft    " LINK "TopLeft"} - move window to left upper corner of screen

This functions may be installed, but do not need to be installed at all.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Einstellungen" "Preferences"
@{b}@{u}Preferences@{uu}@{ub}

 The preference-settings are really simple. Mark the @{b}WinCommodity@{ub}-Icon by clicking on it once with your mouse. Call the menuitem 'Pictogram/Information'. Now you can edit the Icon-Tooltypes. The included Icon has all possible Tooltypes entered, y
ou need only to change them for your wishes, if necessary. So, if you want to change a Hotkey, it need to be named it the following format:
@{b}@{i}<CX_FUNCTIONNAME=rawkey> + your keycombination@{ui}@{ub}
Here you have to enter standard workbench-key-names! (i.e. 'lalt' for the left Alt key, 'lcommand' for the left Amiga key). If you have set all preferences, click on the Gadget 'Save' and the changes will take effect at next start of @{b}WinCommodity@{ub}
.

 The installed key-combinations may be shown while @{b}WinCommodity@{ub} is running. Herefore you have to call the GUI of @{b}WinCommodity@{ub}. Since there is no Hotkey for the GUI you have to do this via the Commodity-Control-Program 'Exchange'. (In my 
opinion there is no sense in making a hotkey for a gui, I may need once a month, if I would need as often...)                             
 If this GUI is called, a requester appears, which shows all disposable functions and its hotkeys. If a hotkey has not been accepted by the program, the function is not disposable and the requester says 'NOT INSTALLED' for this feature.

 Example-Configuration:
 @{"CX_CENTERKEY     " LINK "CX_CENTERKEY" 0} -- F1
 @{"CX_CLOSEACTIVEWIN" LINK "CX_CLOSEACTIVEWIN" 0} -- Control w
 @{"CX_CLOSEWBWINS   " LINK "CX_CLOSEWBWINS" 0} -- Control LAmiga w
 @{"CX_PARENTKEY     " LINK "CX_PARENTKEY" 0} -- F2
 @{"CX_PRIORITY      " LINK "CX_PRIORITY" 0} -- 0
 @{"CX_TOGGLEKEY     " LINK "CX_TOGGLEKEY" 0} -- LAlt Tabulator
 @{"CX_ZIPKEY        " LINK "CX_ZIPKEY" 0} -- F3
 @{"CX_TOPLEFTKEY    " LINK "CX_TOPLEFT" 0} -- Control F2
 @{"OFFSET           " LINK "OFFSET" 0} -- 5
@ENDNODE

@NODE "TopLeft" "TopLeft"
@{b}@{u}TopLeft@{uu}@{ub}

This function moves the active window to the left top border of its screen. But @{b}WinCommodity@{ub} does not choose the physical 0,0-position of the screen, it chooses the position directly below the ScreenBar.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "ToggleWins" "ToggleWins"
@{b}@{u}ToggleWins@{uu}@{ub}

This function toggles between the windows. If called, the next window in screens window-structure will be activated an popped to front. @{b}WinCommodity@{ub} cares about borderless or backdrop-windows and does not activate them.

(This funtion has been adapted from X-Windows)
@ENDNODE

@NODE "CloseWBWins" "CloseWBWins"
@{b}@{u}CloseWBWins@{uu}@{ub}

This function is nearly similar to @{"CloseWins" LINK "CloseWins"}, except that @{b}WinCommodity@{ub} does only close Workbench-Windows and does close all it can find (not only the active one). Workbench's main window will not be closed.
The Idea of this function is old, it has been adapted from the MacOS not only once. But I newer before saw such a unction, which does not try to close the Workbench-main-window.

@{i}-->@{ui} Here it is necessary to do a remark. This function is fast! But it may become timeful if you do open too much windows, since it first scans all windows and then it starts closing the Workbenchwindows, beginning with the most back one. Herefor
e it has to allocate memory for each window (for programmers: this is a recursive function). Do, if you have too many windows open, layers.library starts to become slow, because of the lot windows and @{b}WinCommodity@{ub} has to wait for each window to b
e closed. This can take a lot of time. Example: On my machine, an A1200 with 28MHz 68020 processor and 10MB it took around 6 mins to close 60 Workbenchwindows! (But how often do you open more than 60 Workbenchwindows???)
@ENDNODE

@NODE "CloseWin" "CloseWin"
@{b}@{u}CloseWin@{uu}@{ub}

This function does the same as a click on the CloseGadget of a window. 

@{i}1)@{ui} In PageStream3, there is a non-standard system of Inuition-Message-handling. Therefore PageStream3-View-Windows will not be closed - they will be minimized! ...Not my fault.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "CenterWins" "CenterWins"
@{b}@{u}CenterWins@{uu}@{ub}

This function centers the active window on its screen. The screenbar is ignored in the calculation.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "ParentWin" "ParentWin"
@{b}@{u}ParentWin@{uu}@{ub}

This function moves the avtive window below the window-topborder of its parentwindow. This function is really useful, if you want to have some arrangemant in your directory-structure.
If there is no parentwindow, the window will be placed below the screenbar, just like with @{"TopLeft" LINK "TopLeft"}.
In addition to this function, there is the tooltype @{"OFFSET" LINK "OFFSET"}. This is for positioning the windows offsetted (e.g. every daughter window has an horizontal offset of 5 pixels to its parentwindow).
@ENDNODE

@NODE "ZipWin" "ZipWin"
@{b}@{u}ZipWin@{uu}@{ub}

This function does the same as a click on the Zip-Gadget of a window: The window will be sized to minimum/maximum size
@ENDNODE

@NODE "CenterKey"
-@{b}CX_CENTERKEY@{ub}:
 Here you enter the keycombination for the windowcentering.
 If you want to change the presetted value, you have to enter the followin: rawkey, followed by the keys, you want tho activate this function. (i.e. 'rawkey ctrl esc' for Ctrl + ESC keys)
@ENDNODE

