@NODE "Voraussetzungen" "Requirements"
@prev "Main"
@next "Main"
@{u}@{b}Requirements@{ub}@{uu}

You only require Kickstart 2.04 or higher for running @{b}WinCommodity@{ub}

The following System-Libraries will be also required:
       icon.library        v36
       intuition.library   v37
       commodities.library v37
       intuition.library   v37
       dos.library         v37

This librarires are already inside your Amiga, so don't panic if you can't find them in LIBS: (they are in the Kickstart-ROM).
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Benutzung" "Usage"
@prev "Main"
@next "Main"
@{b}@{u}Usage@{uu}@{ub}

 @{b}WinCommodity@{ub} is a Commodity. It may be put into the directory SYS:WBStartup, and will then be loaded after each reset.
 @{b}WinCommodity@{ub} provides its functions via Hotkeys. This Hotkeys are @{"configurable" LINK "Einstellungen"}. It is useful to choose this Hotkeys in a easy to reach and also logical way. The included Icon has a demo-configuration, which has the foll
owing presets:                      

 @{"CX_CENTERKEY     " LINK "CX_CENTERKEY" 0} -- F1
 @{"CX_CLOSEACTIVEWIN" LINK "CX_CLOSEACTIVEWIN" 0} -- Control w
 @{"CX_CLOSEWBWINS   " LINK "CX_CLOSEWBWINS" 0} -- Control LAmiga w
 @{"CX_PARENTKEY     " LINK "CX_PARENTKEY" 0} -- F2
 @{"CX_PRIORITY      " LINK "CX_PRIORITY" 0} -- 0
 @{"CX_TOGGLEKEY     " LINK "CX_TOGGLEKEY" 0} -- LAlt Tabulator
 @{"CX_ZIPKEY        " LINK "CX_ZIPKEY" 0} -- F3
 @{"CX_TOPLEFTKEY    " LINK "CX_TOPLEFT" 0} -- Control F2
 @{"OFFSET           " LINK "OFFSET" 0} -- 5

 As a Commodity, @{b}WinCommodity@{ub} is accesable via the 'Exchange'-Utility. Here you also can activate the GUI of @{b}WinCommodity@{ub}. With 'Exchange' you can quit @{b}WinCommodity@{ub}, if this would ever be necessary. @{b}WinCommodity@{ub} also qu
its for itself if you start it twice. (without any notice!)
 Calling the functions is really easy after starting @{b}WinCommodity@{ub}: Press the Hotkey-combination of your choice and its function will be called.
@{i}Example:@{ui} For centering the active window, press 'F1'. The window will be centered right now.
 Now there should be no more problem using @{b}WinCommodity@{ub}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "OFFSET"
-@{b}OFFSET@{ub}:
 The offset to left border by positioning the window below the parent window if you call @{"ParentWin()" LINK "Parentwin"}.
 The priority, the Commodity will get in the AmigaOS. It is presetted to '0'. If you can't handle the term 'priority', be aware of this value!
@ENDNODE


@NODE "CX_PRIORITY"
-@{b}CX_PRIORITY@{ub}:
 The priority, the Commodity will get in the AmigaOS. It is presetted to '0'. If you can't handle the term 'priority', be aware of this value!
@ENDNODE


@NODE "CX_CENTERKEY"
-@{b}CX_CENTERKEY@{ub}:
 Here you enter the Hotkey for window centering.

 If you want to change the presetted value, you have to enter the followin: rawkey, followed by the keys, you want tho activate this function. (i.e. 'rawkey ctrl esc' for Ctrl + ESC keys)
@ENDNODE

@NODE "CX_PARENTKEY"
-@{b}CX_PARENTKEY@{ub}:
 Here you enter the Hotkey for the windowmoving below its parenwindow. The parentwindow is the window which is directly parent to the active one, so it need'nt to be the physical parent one                                               

 If you want to change the presetted value, you have to enter the followin: rawkey, followed by the keys, you want tho activate this function. (i.e. 'rawkey ctrl esc' for Ctrl + ESC keys)
@ENDNODE

@NODE "CX_ZIPKEY"
-@{b}CX_ZIPKEY@{ub}:
 Here you enter the Hotkey for Ziping the window.

 If you want to change the presetted value, you have to enter the followin: rawkey, followed by the keys, you want tho activate this function. (i.e. 'rawkey ctrl esc' for Ctrl + ESC keys)
@ENDNODE

@NODE "CX_TOGGLEKEY"
-@{b}CX_TOGGLEKEY@{ub}:
 Here you enter the Hotkey for toggling between the windows.

 If you want to change the presetted value, you have to enter the followin: rawkey, followed by the keys, you want tho activate this function. (i.e. 'rawkey ctrl esc' for Ctrl + ESC keys)
@ENDNODE

@NODE "CX_CLOSEWBWINS"
-@{b}CX_CLOSEWBWINS@{ub}
 Here you enter the Hotkey for closing all Workbench-windows.

 If you want to change the presetted value, you have to enter the followin: rawkey, followed by the keys, you want tho activate this function. (i.e. 'rawkey ctrl esc' for Ctrl + ESC keys)
@ENDNODE

@NODE "CX_CLOSEACTIVEWIN"
-@{b}CX_CLOSEACTIVEWIN@{ub}
 Here you enter the Hotkey for closing the active window.

 If you want to change the presetted value, you have to enter the followin: rawkey, followed by the keys, you want tho activate this function. (i.e. 'rawkey ctrl esc' for Ctrl + ESC keys)
@ENDNODE

@NODE "CX_TOPLEFT"
-@{b}CX_TOPLEFT@{ub}
 Here you enter the Hotkey for moving the window on the left border below the screenbar.

 If you want to change the presetted value, you have to enter the followin: rawkey, followed by the keys, you want tho activate this function. (i.e. 'rawkey ctrl esc' for Ctrl + ESC keys)
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Installation" "Installation"
@{b}@{u}Installation@{uu}@{ub}

Simply use the Installer-Script, I hardly tried to create one which is perfect for the first installation as also for updates.
(You will need the 'Commodore Installer' for this script)

If you really don't want to use this Script, you should put the Program to the directory you want to have it to and put the file 'WinCommodity_eng.Guide' to your documentation-directory (usually this is 'HELP:')

There are some files in the directory which will not be copied, but may be interesting for you:
 - 'CHANGES'   a german textfile withe the last changes in the program
 - '.HISTORY'  the full history of @{b}WinCommodity@{ub} (in english)


If you are a programmer, the 'dev/' directory may be interesting for you. There are includes for AmigaE in 68000, 68020 and 68040-version and also autodocs in AmigaGuide© format.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "BUGS" "Bugs"
@prev "Main"
@next "Main"
@{b}@{u}Bugs@{uu}@{ub}

Oh, there are BUGS in this version. Some Betatesters found them, and I 
have to list them now:

- the Bug
* comment to the Bug
** solution

-CloseWin()
If you try to close a CON-Window (a really normal Amiga-DOS Shell) you 
will get an GURU 80000004 (illegal processor instruction).
* This is a BUG of AmigaDOS, so I have to find a solution for it, which 
may take longer...
** The only Tip, I can give is: use KingCon as me and this will make no 
problems

-CloseWin()
This function will not close any window which is called "Workbench"
* well, this is really a mistake of mine i will fix this...
** do not call any drawer or partition "Workbench"


-WinCommodity Info
If you open the Info Requester Wincommodity is disabled for this time but 
the HotKeys are cached all the time this window is open. If you press 
some Hotkeys in this time, they all will be executed after closing the 
About-Requester. So it may occure a guru due to operations which are done 
to already close windows
* This is not easy for me to solve, but i'll work on it
** Please do not activate any functions when About is open
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Zukunft" "The future"
@prev "Main"
@next "Main"
@{b}@{u}The future@{uu}@{ub}

The future of WinCommodity belongs to you. If I will get enough feedback and some new ideas, I will continue developing. If there are any bugreports, I will fix that bugs and make a new version.
@{b}WinCommodity@{ub} is MAILWARE and will stay MAILWARE. It will not become Shareware at any time!

If you have any idea for @{b}WinCommodity@{ub}, send it to @{"me" LINK Addy}!
@ENDNODE

